
[1]honey

   HON'EY, n. hun'y.

   1. A sweet vegetable juice, collected by bees from the flowers of
   plants, and deposited in cells of the comb in hives. Honey, when pure,
   is of a moderate consistence, of a whitish color,tinged with
   yellow,sweet to the taste, of an agreeable smell, soluble in water, and
   becoming vinous by fermentation. In medicine, it is useful as a
   detergent and aperient. It is supposed to consist of sugar, mucilage,
   and an acid.

   2. Sweetness; lusciousness.

   The king hath found

   Matter against him, that forever mars

   The honey of his language.

   3. A word of tenderness; sweetness; sweet one.

                 HON'EY, v.t. To talk fondly. [Little used.]

   1. To sweeten.
